                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> As an ex-prison guard I just have to say one thing, 99% of those jack asses need to be there. This might be kinda skewed as I worked in the 3rd most violent prison in the USA.<br /><br />However, prisoners have some insane rights once they get in, more than the guards. They get 10 dollar dentist visits, free allergy shots, 5 dollar doctor visits, and a slew of other rights, oh yea free basic cable. <br /><br />They can shop at the prison store and buy canned goods, bread, cokes, and other such things. Only the bottom 2 custody levels spend all thier time in their cell.<br /><br />Side note we were so overcrowded with the bottom 2 custody levels that we started to reclassify inmates (ones that should be handled with 2 guards and cuffs the whole time) to medium custody (where I worked) where they only spend 10 hours of the day in thier cell.<br /><br />As it stood I was on a wing of 64ish inmates armed only with a ball point pen and my attitude. Yes they were all out walking around when they got back from work and I had to make sure they got showers, 4 hours of TV and outside rec time.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
