                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> "Would you need more lawyers and cops, or less lawyers and cops? And Judges? More or less?"<br /><br />Less or around the same amount, consider most of the people that actually goto jail for an extended period of time are "poor" or low middle class. That + the fact they make money on each prisoner they keep along with all the extra parts that screw over families and such. Ie at&t or verison has a deal with x prison for all outgoing calls and charges double the rate for long distance ect, and the fact they have to make a collect call makes it worse. My cousin got locked up a while ago and he called me one time for 10 minutes and it cost ME 68$ to find out he got in trouble. So not only am I unable to see one of my only living family members (not that he didnt do anything wrong cause he did) I should be charged an obscene amount just for the privelege to hear he is still alive? Or how i come to find out he needs to "buy" prison shoes or clothes which are shitty and cost like 80$ for what ammount to a white pair of keds that you can get for 5$...<br /><br />There is a website devoted to the scamm that is the US prison system it deals mainly with prisons in pennsillvania &lt;sp&gt; and how the guards/warden ect steal millions of dollars a year from the prison. Like truckloads of food and such are delivered to the wardens house instead of the prison, they spent 60g's on a party and somehow they needed 40 cases of peanut butter but of those 40 cases only 3 made it to the party and all types of shit like that. I am SURE this is not only containted to one state, it's the basis of the entire system prisoners should be treated poorly and the "higher up's" should reap the rewards of these lost causes that are the prisoners...<br /><br />The really funny part to me is, what ever happend to the guys from enron, or any other robber baron that has made off with millions of inverstors money/savings. Or how about that guy that got paid 200 million a year to "monitor/review" the trading practices of the entire NY stock exchange. Nothing has happend or will happen EVER, everyone that isn't rich as all hell will get the shaft every time and we will watch and say oh that sucks too bad things are so crooked.... <br />I'm glad people are being rehabilitated, but imo they are only making an army of men/women who would like nothing less then to see the entire establishment burn down.<br /><br />"As it stood I was on a wing of 64ish inmates armed only with a ball point pen and my attitude. Yes they were all out walking around when they got back from work and I had to make sure they got showers, 4 hours of TV and outside rec time."<br /><br />See that is bullshit and I am glad you didn't get into any bad situations, it just goes to show the top 1% of the country doesn't mind fucking over the working guy in the name of justice. I truely feel bad for prison guards (most of them anyhow) since they are caught in the middle of all this most are family men that deserve something more then a fucking ball point pen to ward off 64 guys who would beat/kill them just on principle.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
